---
const title = "SSGC Bill Online — Check Sui Southern Gas Bill Karachi March 2026";
const desc = "Check your SSGC gas bill online by 10-digit consumer number. View your Sui Southern Gas Company bill for Karachi, Sindh, and Balochistan — free, no login required.";
const canonical = "https://pakistanbill.online/ssgc-bill/";

const faqSchema = {
  "@context": "https://schema.org",
  "@type": "FAQPage",
  "mainEntity": [
    { "@type": "Question", "name": "How do I check my SSGC gas bill online?", "acceptedAnswer": { "@type": "Answer", "text": "Visit ssgc.com.pk, go to Online Services and click View Bill. Enter your 10-digit SSGC consumer number printed on any previous gas bill and click Submit. Your SSGC bill appears with amount, due date, meter readings, and consumption in MMBTU." } },
    { "@type": "Question", "name": "What is the SSGC consumer number format?", "acceptedAnswer": { "@type": "Answer", "text": "SSGC consumer numbers are 10 digits long — different from SNGPL which uses 11 digits. Your consumer number is printed at the top of every SSGC gas bill. Save it in your phone for monthly bill checking." } },
    { "@type": "Question", "name": "What is SSGC helpline number?", "acceptedAnswer": { "@type": "Answer", "text": "SSGC helpline is 1199 — same as SNGPL. Available 24/7 for gas leakage emergencies, billing complaints, and new connection queries." } },
  ]
};

const faqs = [
  { q: "How do I check my SSGC gas bill online in March 2026?", a: "Visit ssgc.com.pk → Online Services → View Bill. Enter your 10-digit SSGC consumer number (printed on the top of any previous gas bill) and click Submit. Your complete SSGC bill for March 2026 appears with amount due, due date, meter readings, MMBTU consumption, and all charges. You can also use the SSGC Connect app on Android and iOS." },
  { q: "Where do I find my SSGC 10-digit consumer number?", a: "Your SSGC consumer number is a 10-digit number printed prominently on the top section of every SSGC gas bill — on the right side near your name and address. SSGC uses 10 digits — unlike SNGPL which uses 11 digits. If you have lost all previous bills, call SSGC helpline 1199 with your CNIC and address to retrieve it." },
  { q: "What areas does SSGC supply gas to?", a: "SSGC (Sui Southern Gas Company) supplies gas to Karachi (all areas), interior Sindh (Hyderabad, Sukkur, Larkana, Mirpurkhas), and Balochistan (Quetta, Hub, Khuzdar, and other cities with pipeline access). SNGPL, not SSGC, supplies Punjab, KPK, Islamabad, and AJK." },
  { q: "What is the difference between SSGC and SNGPL?", a: "SSGC (Sui Southern Gas Company) covers Karachi, Sindh, and Balochistan — the southern half of Pakistan. SNGPL (Sui Northern Gas Pipelines Limited) covers Punjab, KPK, Islamabad, and AJK — the northern half. If you live in Karachi, Hyderabad, or Quetta, your gas is SSGC. If you live in Lahore, Islamabad, or Peshawar, your gas is SNGPL." },
  { q: "What is SSGC eBill and how do I subscribe?", a: "SSGC eBill is a service that sends your gas bill by email or SMS every month. To subscribe, register at ssgc.com.pk → Customer Services → eBill. Enter your consumer number, email address, and mobile number. Once registered, SSGC sends your bill directly to your phone and email — eliminating dependence on postal delivery." },
  { q: "What is the SSGC Connect app?", a: "SSGC Connect is SSGC's official mobile app available on Android (Google Play) and iOS (App Store). After registering with your 10-digit consumer number and CNIC, you can view bills, pay online, track complaints, request duplicate bills, submit meter reading photos, and check gas supply status — all in one place." },
  { q: "What is MMBTU on my SSGC bill?", a: "MMBTU (Million British Thermal Units) is the unit SSGC uses for billing. Your gas meter measures consumption in HCFT (Hundred Cubic Feet). SSGC converts this to MMBTU for tariff calculation. 1 MMBTU ≈ 10.03 HCFT of gas. Your bill shows both the meter reading in HCFT and the billing quantity in MMBTU." },
  { q: "How do I pay my SSGC gas bill online in Karachi?", a: "Pay through JazzCash, Easypaisa, or any bank mobile app. Go to Bill Payments, select Gas, choose SSGC, enter your 10-digit consumer number, verify the amount, and confirm. HBL, MCB, Meezan, UBL, Bank Alfalah, and all major Karachi banks support SSGC bill payment. You can also pay via the SSGC Connect app or at any SSGC regional office." },
  { q: "Why is my SSGC gas bill so high in winter?", a: "SSGC Karachi winters are milder than northern Pakistan — gas heating demand in Karachi is relatively low. However, interior Sindh and Balochistan winters are cold, and gas usage for room heating and geysers spikes significantly. For Karachi consumers: high winter bills are usually due to geyser use. If your Protected status changes to Unprotected (average exceeds 0.5 HCFT/day), your rate multiplies by 4-5x — this is the most common cause of bill shocks." },
  { q: "How do I report a gas emergency to SSGC?", a: "Call SSGC emergency helpline 1199 immediately if you smell gas or suspect a leak. Turn off all gas appliances, open windows, do not use electrical switches, and evacuate the area. SSGC has 24/7 emergency response teams in Karachi and all major SSGC cities. In Karachi, response time is typically 20–45 minutes for emergencies." },
  { q: "How do I apply for a new SSGC gas connection in Karachi?", a: "Apply online at ssgc.com.pk → New Connection, or visit your nearest SSGC regional office in Karachi (Gulshan, SITE, Korangi, Clifton, and other areas). Required documents: CNIC copy, property ownership or tenancy agreement, and site layout. Connection fees depend on your distance from the nearest gas main. Urban Karachi connections typically take 30–90 days." },
  { q: "How do I file an SSGC billing complaint?", a: "Call 1199 with your 10-digit consumer number. Explain the issue and get a complaint reference number. If unresolved within 14 working days, escalate to OGRA (Oil & Gas Regulatory Authority) at 0800-66256 (toll-free) or file at ogra.org.pk. OGRA has legal authority over SSGC and its decisions are binding." },
];
