  <div class="container" style="padding:3rem 1rem;display:grid;grid-template-columns:2fr 1fr;gap:2.5rem;max-width:1200px;margin:0 auto;">
    <div>
      <section id="about" style="margin-bottom:3rem;">
        <h2 style="font-size:1.6rem;font-weight:800;margin-bottom:1rem;color:#1a3a5c;">About SSGC — Sui Southern Gas Company</h2>
        <p>Sui Southern Gas Company (SSGC) is Pakistan's second-largest gas utility, supplying gas to over <strong>3.5 million consumers</strong> across <strong>Karachi</strong>, <strong>Sindh</strong>, and <strong>Balochistan</strong>. Incorporated in 1954 — the same year the famous Sui gas field in Balochistan was discovered — SSGC was the first company to harness Pakistan's natural gas for domestic and industrial use. The Sui gas field, located in Dera Bugti district, initially powered Karachi and remained Pakistan's primary gas source for decades.</p>
        <p>SSGC's service area includes: all of <strong>Karachi</strong> (Pakistan's largest city and commercial capital), <strong>Hyderabad</strong>, <strong>Sukkur</strong>, <strong>Larkana</strong>, <strong>Mirpurkhas</strong>, <strong>Nawabshah</strong>, and all major Sindh cities; and in Balochistan — <strong>Quetta</strong>, <strong>Hub</strong>, <strong>Turbat</strong>, <strong>Khuzdar</strong>, and all cities with pipeline access. SSGC also supplies major industrial areas including <strong>SITE Industrial Area</strong>, <strong>Korangi Industrial Area</strong>, and <strong>Landhi Industrial Area</strong> — Karachi's three major manufacturing zones.</p>
        <p>SSGC operates the <strong>eBill service</strong> (email + SMS bill delivery) and the <strong>SSGC Connect app</strong> for digital bill management. Gas regulation in Pakistan is handled by <strong>OGRA</strong> (Oil and Gas Regulatory Authority), which sets SSGC's tariffs and handles consumer escalations at <strong>0800-66256</strong>.</p>
      </section>

      <section id="how-to" style="margin-bottom:3rem;">
